- Distribution centers should be able to manage inventory and prepare orders/
- Delivery drivers should be able to accept assignments, pick up orders, and navigate to the customerâ€™s location.
Be sure to consider edge cases such as high order volumes, inventory consistency, driver assignment, and failures (e.g., payment errors, out-of-stock items, or driver cancellations).
- Customer should be able to browse, place, and track orders
- DCs should be able to manange inventory and receive/prepare customer orders
- Drivers should be able to self-accept orders from DCs and deliver to customer
- System should be able to scale to support busy peaks
- System should be highly available for notifications and requests
- System should be highly consistent for orders
